            <pb n="3" facs="#f0001"/>
            <cb/>
            <milestone unit="section" rendition="#hr"/>
            <lb break="yes"/>
            <p>
                <hi rendition="#c">FROM A LATE LONDON PAPER.</hi>
            </p>
            <lb break="yes"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Extent and Population of America.</hi>
                </head>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The @ollwing estimate of the extent, in<lb break="yes"/>square leagues, and population, of the Con-<lb break="no"/>tinent of America in 1822, was lately trans-<lb break="no"/>mitted by Baron de Humboldt from Paris,<lb break="yes" />to President Bolivar, with the accompany-<lb break="no"/>ing letter.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2"> </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#i">Sq. Leagues</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#i">Population</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Mexico, or New Spain,</cell>
                        <cell>75,630</cell>
                        <cell>6,800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Guate@ala.</cell>
                        <cell>16,740</cell>
                        <cell>1,600,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Cuba and Porto Rico,</cell>
                        <cell>4,430</cell>
                        <cell>800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell rows="2" rendition="#rightBraced">Colombia</cell>
                        <cell>Venez@ela,</cell>
                        <cell>33,700</cell>
                        <cell>900,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>N. Grenada,</cell>
                        <cell>58,250</cell>
                        <cell>1,800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Per@.</cell>
                        <cell>42,150</cell>
                        <cell>1,400,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Chili,</cell>
                        <cell>14,240</cell>
                        <cell>1,100,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">@enos Ayres,</cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#u">126,770</hi>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#u">2,000,000</hi>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Total formerly Spanish,</cell>
                        <cell>372,140</cell>
                        <cell>16,100,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">United States,</cell>
                        <cell>125,440</cell>
                        <cell>10,200,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell cols="2">Brazil,</cell>
                        <cell>266,990</cell>
                        <cell>4,000,000</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The above surfaces have been calculated<lb break="yes"/>with great care, on maps rectified by astro-<lb break="no"/>nomical observations. The calculations have<lb break="yes"/>been several times repeated by M. Mathieu,<lb break="yes"/>Member of the Board of Longitude and o@<lb break="yes"/>the Institute, as well as by myself. The<lb break="yes"/>results differ from those published in 1809<lb break="yes"/>in the Political Essay on Mexico. Then<lb break="yes"/>the inhabited parts @one had been calcula-<lb break="no"/>
                    <cb/> ted, without @ling the de@ regi@,<lb break="yes"/>over which the independent tribes of the<lb break="yes"/>indigenous inbabitants wander. Now the<lb break="yes"/>whole extent of each country, to its furthest<lb break="yes"/>limits, has been m@asured.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The population of the different parts of<lb break="yes"/>
                    <hi rendition="#i">cidevant</hi> Spanish America is very uncer-<lb break="no" />tain, nevertheless each portion has been cal-<lb break="no"/>culated according to the Iatest data which<lb break="yes"/>have re@ched me.&#x2014;The present estimate<lb break="yes"/>ought to be considered in the same light as<lb break="yes"/>all my other works on America; they are not<lb break="yes" />like other essays, in which every thing will<lb break="yes"/>have to be done over again. Statistical calcu-<lb break="no"/>lation can only be rendered perfect by de-<lb break="no"/>grees in like manner as the elements of me-<lb break="no"/>teorological and astronomical tables.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Comparison.</hi>&#x2014;&#x2014;Sp@n contains 16,094<lb break="yes"/>square legues&#x2014;&#x2014;Europe contains. 304,710<lb break="yes"/>square le@gues, and the whole of South A-<lb break="no"/>merica 581,891 square leagues. [Square]</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <hi rendition="#et">HUMBOLDT</hi>
                    </salute>
                </closer>
            </div>
            <lb break="yes"/>
